The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, August 11, 2003 				 Traffic bane of bustling town
		 DAILY DREAD: Vehicles  standing fender-to-fender for hours on end are a characteristic  sight on the other side of the Hooghly. Pictures by  Kishor Roy ChowdhurySamir Chakraborty: No resident of Howrah can reach his or her destination without a delay of at least an hour. Traffic jams are not peculiar around Howrah station alone, but also at places like Mullick Phatak. What can be done about it?																																																													Actually, traffic in Howrah is a serious problem and we are very concerned about it. We dont have an adequate traffic control system in place to tackle such a heavy flow of vehicles. However, we are trying to ease the situation.
